---
// HOME Beat 3 — where it goes. Vision register. Heading over body, left on rail.
// Future tense on prediction; shape only, no magnitudes.
---

<section class="px-6 py-8 md:px-10 md:py-12">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[72rem]">
    <div class="rise h-px w-16 bg-accent"></div>
    <h2
      class="rise mt-7 max-w-[42rem] text-balance font-display text-3xl font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] text-ink md:text-[2.5rem]"
      style="animation-delay: 80ms"
    >
      Measurement now. Prediction next.
    </h2>
    <p
      class="rise mt-6 max-w-[46rem] text-lg leading-[1.75] text-muted"
      style="animation-delay: 160ms"
    >
      Measuring this supply is real today. What it unlocks is bigger: a kind of
      data that didn't exist before, across enough proteins and systems to learn
      the rules connecting a sequence to how well a cell can build it. Every
      protein measured sharpens the next prediction. The goal: design for
      manufacturability from the start, instead of discovering it at the bench.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
